summary:
•	Africa Sub-Sahara
 28 years of working experience in 16 African countries, in particular in the Eastern and Southern regions of Africa Sub-Sahara; In-depth knowledge of socio-economic, cultural, and political developments and the business climate in these countries. 

•	Design and implementation of Business Development Strategies
Advising local consultancies companies in Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda and Rwanda on management and business development strategies; developing and implementing commercial and business development strategies for HTSPE; “commodisation” of the acquisition process for faster and cheaper production of high quality tenders with a higher win ratio and improved margins; In-depth knowledge of and expertise with developing successful commercial offerings for various donor clients;

•	Management
Project/Programme Management and Change Management at field level, Bid and Contract Manager at office level. Over the past 10 years involved in winning assignments with a total contract value of over £120 million; Systematic coaching and mentoring of young graduates in all aspects of the consultancy business;

•	Aid Policies 
Expert of the multilateral and bilateral aid market, its policies and delivery mechanisms and the procurement rules and regulations of all major donors: DFID, EC (EDF), WB, MCC, GIZ, DANIDA, AusAID and SIDA; 

•	Natural Resources Management (NRM)  
Agricultural engineering background in tropical and sub-tropical agriculture and farming systems; In-depth knowledge of and experience with land and forestry sector. In the land sector closely involved in the ground breaking Land Tenure Regularisation (LTR) programme, Rwanda, 2005 – 2012. In the forestry sector successfully managed the WB funded Forest Resources Management Project (FRMP), Tanzania, 1994 – 1998; expertise in sustainable and community based forest management approaches  and charcoal production systems and its trade and consumption patterns.
